 The Study Drug: Bevacizumab is designed to prevent or slow down the growth of cancer cells by blocking the growth of blood vessels.

 Study Drug Administration: If you are found to be eligible to take part in this study, every 2 weeks, you will receive bevacizumab by vein over about 1 hour.

